info.headline: Flood Advisory issued September 26 at 8:14PM EDT until September 26 at 10:15PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee FL
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...Portions of Panhandle Florida, including the following county, Jackson and southwest Georgia, including the following county, Seminole.
* WHEN...Until 1015 PM EDT /915 PM CDT/.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 814 PM EDT /714 PM CDT/, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the advisory area. Between 1 and 2.5 inches of rain have fallen. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Chattahoochee, Sneads, Grand Ridge, Fairchild, Drakes Still, Seminole State Park, Haynes, Desser, Lake Seminole and Cypress. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction:
Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.
Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.
Please report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and request they pass this information to the National Weather Service when you can do so safely.

parameter.value: FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 1015 PM EDT /915 PM CDT/ THIS EVENING
